    <div class="div-body">
      <div class="div-html">
        <h2>HTML Summary</h2>
        <div
          >HTML (HyperText Markup Language) is used to define our page content,
          structure and meaning. You don't use it for styling purposes. Use CSS
          for that instead!
        </div>
        <dl>
          <dt
            >You don't use it for styling purposes. Use CSS for that instead!
          </dt>
          <dd class="orange"
            >HTML uses "elements" to describe (annotate) content</dd
          >
          <dd class="space"
            >HTML elements typically have an opening tag, content and then a
            closing tag
          </dd>
          <dd class="orange"
            >You can also have void (empty) elements like images
          </dd>
          <dd class="orange"
            >You can also configure elements with attributes
          </dd>
          <dd class="space"
            >There's a long list of available elements but you'll gain
            experience over time, no worries
          </dd>
          <dt
            >Learn more about all available HTML elements on
            <a
              id="mnd-html-link"
              href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML"
              target="_blank"
            >
              the MDN HTML element reference
            </a>
          </dt>
        </dl>
      </div>
      <div class="div-css">
        <div>
          <h2>CSS Summary</h2>
          <dl>
            <dt
              >CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used for styling our page content
            </dt>
            <dd class="space">Styles are assigned via property-value pairs </dd>
            <dd class="space"
              >You can assign styles via the "style" attributes
            </dd>
            <dd class="orange"
              >To avoid code duplication, you typically use global styles (e.g.
              via the "style" element) instead
            </dd>
            <dd
              >Alternatively, you can work with external stylesheet files which
              you "link" to
            </dd>
            <dd class="orange"
              >When working with CSS, concepts like "inheritance", "specificity"
              and the "box model" should be understood
            </dd>
            <dt
              >Learn more about all available CSS elements on
              <a
                id="mnd-html-link"
                href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS?retiredLocale=vi"
                target="_blank"
              >
                the MDN CSS element reference
              </a>
            </dt>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
